shire): variant of   Keith  ."]},{"name":"Kite","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>kete</i>, <i>kyte</i> ‘kite’ (the bird of prey), perhaps a nickname for a rapacious person.","Americanized form of German   Keith  .","English: habitational name from one or more of the minor places with names deriving from Old English <i>cȳte</i>, <i>cyte</i> ‘cottage, hut, shed’, such as Kite Farm in Swalecliffe (Kent)."]},{"name":"Keeth","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Keith  ."]},{"name":"Keitt","meanings":["Possibly an altered form of German   Keith   2."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Earl Herveus de Keith I Marishal of Scotland was born in 1080, in Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland, his father, Warin de Keith, was 24 and his mother, Moddan, was 21. He married Martha Adam in 1108, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1139, in his hometown, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1080–1139":"1080–1139","1105–Male":"1105–Surnud","–1090":"–1090","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1057–1140":"1057–1140","1060–Female":"1060–Surnud","1080":"1080","1139":"1139","1090":"1090","about 1109":"umbes 1109","1105":"1105","1057":"1057","1196":"1196","1140":"1140","1060":"1060","1109":"1109","1108":"1108","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1080–1139":"1080–1139","1105–Male":"1105–Kuollut","–1090":"–1090","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1109–1196":"1109–1196","1057–1140":"1057–1140","1060–Female":"1060–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1139":"1139","1090":"1090","about 1109":"noin 1109","1105":"1105","1057":"1057","1196":"1196","1140":"1140","1060":"1060","1109":"1109","1108":"1108","Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Humbie, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1080–1139":"1080–1139","1105–Male":"110